of the’) and the suffix <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Portmann","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Helmut, Franz, Hansi, Kurt.","North German: occupational name for a gatekeeper, from Middle Low German <i>port(e)</i> ‘gate’ (from Latin <i>porta</i>) + <i>man</i> ‘man’, or a topographic name for someone who lived near the gates of a fortified town. Compare   Porter  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":10,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Portman was born in 1445, in London The Temple, Middlesex, England, his father, Walter Portman, was 41 and his mother, Christian Orchard, was 11442. He had at least 1 son with Alice Knoell. He died on 5 June 1521, at the age of 76, and was buried in London, Sumner, Kansas, United States."},"et":{"1445–5 jun 1521":"1445–5. juuni 1521","1445–1521":"1445–1521","1470–1559":"1470–1559","1496–1557":"1496–1557","1404–1474":"1404–1474","1407–1472":"1407–1472","7 May 1472":"7. mai 1472","before 1440":"enne 1440","1472":"1472","1470":"1470","5 jun 1521":"5. juuni 1521","1404":"1404","1557":"1557","1445":"1445","1455":"1455","1521":"1521","1474":"14